    "reply_subject": null,
    "reply_body_html": "<html class=\"apple-mail-supports-explicit-dark-mode\"><head><meta http-equiv=\"content-type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"></head><body dir=\"auto\"><div dir=\"ltr\"></div><div dir=\"ltr\">What a killer email!!!</div><div dir=\"ltr\"><br><blockquote type=\"cite\">On Mar 2, 2026, at 11:56, Christie Johansen-Pinney &lt;christie@growthroosterpunk.com&gt; wrote:<br><br></blockquote></div><blockquote type=\"cite\"><div dir=\"ltr\">﻿\r\n  \r\n  \r\n    <title>RE: fellers inventory gears</title>\r\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\r\n     <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\r\n      \r\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <div>Hello Alex,</div><div><br></div><div>{\"company_name\":\"ShipHawk\",\"industry\":\"Information Technology &amp; Services\",\"email_1_hook\":{\"line_1\":\"ShipHawk is building an order fulfillment operating system that unifies WMS and TMS functions, which is a departure from most logistics software companies that sell separate point solutions for warehouse and shipping management.\",\"line_2\":\"What makes that smart is it addresses the reality that fulfillment is a single continuous process, not a series of disconnected handoffs, which removes the integration friction that typically slows down high-growth shippers.\",\"insight_explanation\":\"This hook identifies ShipHawk's strategic bet on platform consolidation over the industry's traditional best-of-breed approach.\"},\"email_2_hook\":{\"brand_research_line\":\"From your site, ShipHawk comes across as positioning itself as the fulfillment partner for companies that need mega-retailer capabilities without the enterprise complexity, which is a sharp way to own the underserved middle market in the Information Technology &amp; Services space.\",\"insight_explanation\":\"This line reveals ShipHawk's brand psychology of democratizing sophisticated logistics for independent businesses that feel outgunned by larger competitors.\"},\"cross_check\":{\"hooks_feel_distinct\":true,\"email_1_is_strategic_direction\":true,\"email_2_is_brand_psychology\":true,\"swap_test_passed\":true,\"no_shared_website_detail\":true},\"checks\":{\"no_hyphen_character\":true,\"no_exclamation_marks\":true,\"no_question_marks\":true,\"no_quotation_marks\":true,\"no_greeting_or_name\":true,\"no_empty_praise_words\":true,\"no_generic_theme_listing\":true,\"no_banned_phrases\":true,\"no_hype_words\":true,\"contains_genuine_insight_both_hooks\":true,\"not_salesy\":true,\"email_1_does_not_start_with_from_your_site\":true,\"email_2_starts_with_from_your_site\":true,\"email_2_ends_with_industry_space\":true},\"model\":\"xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash\"}</div><div><br></div><div>We're doing deep research into warehouse management software branding right now, and ShipHawk caught our attention as a brand that might find value in what we're putting together. Here's what we'd like to offer completely on us:</div><ul><li style=\"font-weight: 400\">Brand Trends Intelligence Report: What messaging the market is clustering around, which narratives are saturated vs untapped, and what's being overlooked.</li><li style=\"font-weight: 400\">Competitor Positioning Analysis: Share your top three competitors and we'll break down their strengths and weaknesses, and where that leaves room for you.</li><li style=\"font-weight: 400\">AI Brand Clarity Audit: We uncover blind spots you might not realise are there, from how emotionally compelling your brand feels to how well your technical narrative comes across.</li></ul><div>We combine a mix of brand strategists and bespoke AI tools built specifically for branding.</div><div><br></div><div>Just reply with whichever reports sound useful and we'll get cracking.</div><div><br></div><div>Thanks,</div><div>Christie</div><div><br></div><div>P.S. There's something in it for us too. We are learning about warehouse management software branding and hear insights from leaders in the space like yourself.</div><div><br></div><div>Christie Johansen-Pinney</div><div>VP of America</div><div>Rooster Punk</div><div><br></div><br><div class=\"gmail_quote\">\r\n    <div>\r\n      On Thu, Feb 26, 2026 at 08:42 PM UTC Christie Johansen-Pinney &lt;<a href=\"christie@growthroosterpunk.com\">christie@growthroosterpunk.com</a>&gt;  wrote:<br>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <blockquote class=\"gmail_quote\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; border-left:1px solid rgb(204,204,204); padding-left:1ex\"><div>Hello Alex,</div><div><br></div><div>In the webinar about how Fellers scaled smarter, the way you walked through their inventory optimization felt less like a feature list and more like you were showing the actual gears turning behind their operations. It made me picture the real operational drag that companies like Fellers deal with every day.</div><div><br></div><div>It made me think about how the most powerful differentiators in warehouse management are often the ones that solve that kind of operational drag. Which is partly why I've been paying attention to how brands in warehouse management software position themselves.</div><div><br></div><div>I'd love to put together a Brand Trends Intelligence Report for ShipHawk covering the warehouse management software market: specifically the messaging themes dominating the market, which narratives are saturated vs untapped, what's being overlooked and what that could mean for your brand.</div><div><br></div><div>My team at Rooster Punk, a creative agency, create these, and we're doing a handful for the warehouse management software space. Completely on us.</div><div><br></div><div>If that sounds useful, drop me a reply and I'll have my team create it.</div><div><br></div><div>You might be wondering what's in it for us, it's that we'd love to share the insights over a quick call. We're digging deep into how branding is evolving in warehouse management software, and the best insights come from conversations with people like you.</div><div><br></div><div>Best,</div><div>Christie</div><div><br></div><div>p.s That certification milestone must feel like a big win for the whole team.</div><div><br></div><div>Christie Johansen-Pinney</div><div>VP of America</div><div>Rooster Punk</div></blockquote>\r\n    </div>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  </div></blockquote></body></html>",
